rComments: I have no words for this prof. Absolutely brilliant beyond belief. Changed my life. I truly think the only reason people say this is an easy class is because she makes it easy. She makes it easy to show up, to ask questions, to be interested, to want to do well. Prof T. Prof. T. Prof. T. If there is an afterlife you will surely be in heaven.
Best Professor in the entire school! I LOVED HER!!!!!!!!! She taught very well and used engaging materials when teaching. She is extremely respectful and genuinely wants her students to successed

Such a sweet, kind lady. Her course content is quite modern and relevant and her lectures are more so discussions. She really cares about the success of her students and will even grant you an extension if you truly need one. An easy A if you put in even a little bit of effort.
Lit Prof

She teaches in a really modern way, with readings that are super relevant to our pop culture, like Kim Kardashian articles eg. You can tell she's really passionate about writing and she has some good tips to improve your essay writing. She gives great feedback. I found she also wasn't too hard of a marker. Really cares about her students.
She is just so kind and sweet and remembers everyone's name

Shes the sweetest lady Ive ever met, so caring and understanding. Shes completely willing to give extensions on the two papers that semester. I wish she taught more classes so I could have her again!! Take her class!!!! You wont regret it!!!!

Prof T. is an absolute beauty! She helped me out all throughout the semester with feedback and with the papers we had to do in class. She cares about her students more than any prof I've had so far and is a genuinely amazing person. I would 100% recommend taking English with Prof T.
Really sweet Prof that cares about your mark and is very helpful with feedback.

Incredibly sweet prof, truly cares about her students. Remembered my name from the few times I made it to class. Gives amazing feedback on assignments and will edit your work before submission. Chooses interesting (and short!) reading material.

Super lovely lady, makes an attempt to remember everyone!! If you email her she's so considerate and lenient on due dates. Great at getting discussion going, gives great feedback, absolutely take her class!

She has a modern and insightful way of teaching English, instead of reading academic essays like the other sections, we were reading rolling stone articles and reviewing Kanye West lyrics. She's truly caring and understanding. a real gem
Literally one of the sweetest teachers I've ever had. Is very generous about extensions if they are needed and super understanding. She gives good feedback. The biggest of gems.

Prof T is a literal angel sent from above. If you have to take ANY english course, take a class with her. Your writing will drastically improve. She is one of the most genuine people I have ever met. Prof T is especially caring about her students and does what ever she has to so that you can get the help that you need with your writing!

Prof Taylor is a diamond. She is the most caring and compassionate person you could hope to meet. My writing has improved so much from her class. This prof is amazing. Skipping class might not make you fail but she's so nice you'll want to go just to see her.

She is definitely the most selfless prof I had. She cares about her students and was very understanding about everything and anything! Due dates are flexible. She almost always says hi to anyone walking in late, which may be awkward sometimes but you can tell she doesn't mind. Would take her again if she had another class! :)

Super fun lecturer, even though the content gets a bit repetitive. Provides excellent feedback on papers. She had, like, 300 students when I had her, and she still seemed to know the names of everyone in my class (of 75).

Gaye is bar none the best professor I have had at uOttawa. She makes course material interesting and interactive and is extremely caring and attentive to her students. Can't say enough good things. I was in her class over a year ago and she still remembers my name and says hi to me on campus even though she has undoubtedly taught hundreds.

Most compassionate, understanding person I've ever met. Due dates super flexible and exams are easy. Do yourself a favour and take this class. Attendance only mandatory for workshop because of participation grade. Other than that she posts slides online! Offers great feedback on papers and does everything she can to ensure you will succeed!
Prof T is the sweetest women. She really cares about all of her students and wants all of them to succeed. She made this mandatory course bearable, and was really flexible with due dates

She is the by far the best teacher I have ever gotten, she cares about every one of her students and will do anything to have them succeed. One of the most selfless and humble people I have ever met. She is a real 1 and a million teacher! would recommend 100%

Prof T is a blessing you need. She is so understanding and willing to work with you and your struggles. She is flexible but yet has clear expectations. She is amazing and I would recommend her to everyone! TAKE HER CLASS! She is great! Lectures start with music and discussions around them, grading is fair and her assignments catered to everyone.

This woman is an angel!this is an easy A class. She is loving and cares deeply about the success of her student. Tells you exactly what she expects to see in the exam and research papers. When you write your essays and research  paper, send them to her to correct before submitting finally. Take her if you can! Run to her class if you are not there!

Prof T is incredibly caring and genuinely very lovely. You can tell she cares about you as if you're stressed she'll let you hand in a paper late. I've seen students breakdown in front of her and she just comforts them. She also chooses the best course material. I love that we did mostly poems and short stories!

Prof T was one of the sweetest people I've ever met. She really cares about all her students, learns your name, and makes her lectures interesting. She extends deadlines if you ask her to because she wants to see your best work. I wish she taught all my classes. Heavy participation but if you're not comfortable with it, she doesn't pressure you.

Professor Taylor cares about her students, she will take the time to sit down with you and answer any questions. However, her lectures are sporadic and all over the place. She is a very easy grader.  She made the component as small as she could, let's you hand in things late. She is very reassuring for first year students!

Prof T is very caring and will even learn the names of every student in her classes.  The workload for ENG1100 is very light compared to most other classes.  You can tell she is very passionate about teaching and the course.

Prof T is the best prof I've ever had. I didn't do so well on the midterm and she got in touch with me to help. Although I didn't preform too well throughout the course, I did well on the exam and she knew I was seeking her advice. Couldn't believe she gave me an A+! TA marks way harder than her, and make sure she gets to know you and ask for advice

Prof. T. is one of the most caring teachers I've ever had. She really wants you to pass and is a fair grader. She's a little awkward and nervous when in front of the entire class, but is super nice and great one-on-one. The only thing I didn't like about this class was that the TA got to mark my essays instead of her.

I was dreading this class so much, but she honestly made the subject matter tolerable. She tries so hard to make some pretty dull subject matter interesting, and generally speaking succeeded. I had some problems during the semester that made it hard to meet deadlines and she was so kind to me about it. My favourite prof so far.

By far the most caring prof I've had. Even though lectures can be boring, she's so sweet, and kind so they're bearable. Extremely lenient with deadlines to accommodate your schedule, gives great advice, and many chances to give you the best mark possible. Best professor I've had.

Prof T is such a sweetheart and really wants you to do well, she's willing to do what ever it takes to help you and gives extra time if needed. Lectures can be a bit boring but that's just because the material is so dry, she tries her hardest to make it interesting and chooses essays that appeal to the class's interests. Research essay is very long

I absolutely loved prof Taylor!  She is very sweet and caring, and gives excellent feedback on essays.  There is a bit of reading to do in her course pack, but she makes class interesting (even if she is technologically troubled at times).  Wonderful to visit during office hours, she will show full interest in your essay and she helped me a lot.

Prof T is the best! i've taken this course with  a different prof and dropped (thank god!) prof T want you to do better she doesn't care about the grades or deadlines. As long as your writing is improving she will be good with that. Do not take ENG1100 with any other prof. love her 3

I'm an international students, and having a lot of trouble in my language, but she's very very very kind and willing to help me with all problems. She also gives me a lot of chances and time to fix my problems. Greatest teacher I've ever met. You won' t regret to take her lectures.

Professor Taylor is kind, caring, and will do anything in her power to make sure you understand the content and write the best paper you can.  Her feedback on assignments is great.   Her instructions are clear and precise.  She challenges you in class to think about the content (which is interesting and helpful).  One of the best English Profs ever

I LOVE PROF T! She is extraordinarily helpful towards her students! Will literally do ANYTHING in her power to help the students out. Gives amazing feedback on work, super easy to access outside of class! Give her your essays to read before handing in, she will tell you what to fix before grading it! I literally lover her so much

By far one of the sweetest and kindest human beings I've ever met. Cares about her students' success more than anything and will do everything in her power to make sure you reach your full potential. She is very understanding and lenient and gives extensions w/ no questions asked. VERY easy to get an A in her class as long as you put in the effort.

She's great! Really inspirational and not too pretentious about English language like I've found other English profs to be. She's really passionate about the class and is all for writing what you are passionate about. Its really easy to get an A, and I would definitely take any other class she teaches.

Kindest and most caring teacher I have ever had. Constantly went out of her way to help people whenever possible. Kinda boring but that's expected from an essay writing class and 100% worth going out of your way to take a class with her if you get the chance.
She's genuinely the best. She cares so much about the success of her students. Also really great about emailing back quickly and giving amazingly helpful feedback. She's a real gem, 10/10 prof.
Profs Taylor is the best professor I've ever met. She cares about her student a lot and will do whatever she could to help. If you have to take an English course, try to have hers.

She tries to get to know each of her students on a personal level and tries to make the course as easy as possible. The midterm this year is open book and there's no need to even study for it since there's no content to study for (all we're doing is evaluating essays). If you need an extension on an assignment, it's granted.

Prof T was wonderful. She took a 7 to 10 class and made it tolerable. She's very kind, passionate and funny. She's also very understanding, extends deadlines no questions asked. She encourages her students and obviously wants them to do well. Take a class with her if you get the chance! She makes you feel like you belong :)

Prof T. is the most engaging and kind-hearted professor I have ever had. She is the only prof I've had (and will ever have) that learned the names over every person in the large first-year lecture. Do yourself a favour and take Prof T.'s course, she makes English accessible to everyone.

This prof really cares about her students and wants everyone to do well. If you're struggling in the course, talk to her and ask what you can do to improve and she will  do everything in her power to ensure you improve. Gets to know her students and puts names to faces by the end of the class so it feels like you're talking to a friend than a prof

Essay writing is a class I need for my major and I was dreading it. Prof T made this class my favourite to attend even though it was 5:30-8:30 (including dgd). I learned the most in the class and became such a better writer because of her.  She genuinely cares for her students and their success and eventually learns everybody's name.

She is the kindest and nicest person to talk to! Her lectures were interesting and you can tell she really loves what to do! She is a fair marker and gives amazing feedback! I feel like I've become a better writer because of her! I would recommend her to anyone who wants to have a good experience taking an essay writing class!
Prof T is the most understanding professor I've ever had. She really wants her students to succeed and goes out of her way to make sure they do.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Participation matters', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Best prof ever! She is extremely clear on expectations, super sweet and very chill. She makes 8:30 classes bearable. Easy A class. She posts lecture notes online but go to class anyway because sometimes you need to hand in in-class exercise (that's how she takes attendance) which is marked based on effort. Take this course with her if you're ESL.

I never thought I would read about Flappy Bird and the Pope in the same class. She picks things to read and tries to stay relevant to the time. If you have her for the evening, she is a bit tired though. She tries to learn everyone's names and pick essay topics that apply to people's majors and interests.

Professor Taylor is by far the best teacher I have ever had, and the best prof I've met so far at uOttawa.  She is more than fair, so willing to help you with anything you need, and flexible- if you are passionate about a topic, she will let you write an essay on it.  She also learned every one of her student's names after the first class.  Amazing

Sweetest & most understanding prof by far. Has no problem giving extensions on papers if asked ahead of time. Tries to get to know all of her students so speak up in class/DGDs. Very fair marker as fair! uOttawa is lucky to have her! Put in the work, and you'll fly.

Truly a professor that universities and colleges can use more of! The name of the course initially made it seem hard but she was the reason I stuck with it! Attendance wasn't mandatory but I'd highly recommend it as lectures were always fun and she's quite hilarious to boot. Hope I have her again, Prof T deserves a teaching award if you ask me :)
By far my best prof of the semester, not especially easy and she will make you work for your marks, but super helpful, interresting lectures, and she actually cares about her students.
I LOVE LOVE LOVE X 10 TAYLOR GAYE. BEST PROF EVER. RECOMMEND. SWEET AND KIND LADY.

Great prof, learned everyones name in the class. Truly cares about her students and is willing to help. Very passionate about what she is teaching. Probably the only prof I had that made you feel like a person and not just a number.

where do i start, prof T is by far the best prof i have ever had! never liked english class in high school but she made me love her class so much! shes very helpful, she wishes the best for all of her students and wants everyone to succeed. I HIGHLYYYY RECOMMEND HER!!! she deserves the best prof award honestly

She made an 8:30 am Friday morning lecture fun and exciting. The course pack is a selection of articles and essays, and I enjoyed reading them all and discussing them in class. She clearly explains essay structure, grammar, etc., and her exam was super fun to read and analyze! She's super nice and tries to remember everyone's name! Will miss her!!

10/10 would recommend, she is one of the best profs I have ever had. She gets to know everyone's name, and she is extremely understanding and accommodating. She is passionate about what she is teaching, marks fair, if you attend class and put in the effort it will not go unnoticed. Midterm and final are fairly easy, essay topics are interesting.

This prof was hands down the best prof I could ask for. Shes extremely kind and always prepared for her lectures. She takes the time to learn the names of 60+ students and whenever you need the help shes there and is willing to give you extra time :) I would highly recommend taking any of her classes, hoping to have her again in the new few years.
She is my absolute favourite teacher. She is so nice and very helpful! She cares about her students very much and is always there to help when you have questions.
Good lecture but course content is painfully boring plus Prof Taylor sends power point and her lecture notes word by word.

The course material itself isn't the most interesting by its nature, but she makes it as engaging as possible and is just SO nice. She was super understanding and did her best to help and accommodate students - even went so far as to offer new DGD times for us after administration booked a room that was too small. Take her class if you can!

I had Prof T. for an introductory English class and felt lucky to have her as a prof!! She is so kind and really cares about her students. She took the time to learn all her students names and would always give helpful and plentiful feedback. There's nothing good about 8:30 classes, but Prof T. would always be there with a smile.

This professor was incredibly helpful. She was always extremely understanding if you missed a class and welcomed you into her office, even if just to chat. She answered emails very quickly and was a total sweetheart. Show that you're making an effort, and you'll be rewarded.

She care much about international students, she give us some personal help to get good grade, and her tests are not hard, you can get a good grade easily . She is a very kind and responsible professor, I suggest to choose her courses.

Professor Gaye Taylor was the best professor I had this semester. She answers her emails quick and is always willing to help. Not tough on deadlines. Very understanding. Very sweet lady who makes her lectures helpful and engaging. I wish I would have went to class more often.... Give it your all and she awards it. I got 90% and went to class 4x.

LOL I have to say... Prof T is definitely something.. she wears shorts to class and she's so down to earth. She's very understanding and sooooooo sweet as everyone mentioned. I would send her emails asking for her help at 3am an she would always answer them :') absolutely LOVE her. not big on deadlines and give extensions. TAKE HER CLASS IF U CAN!

Doctor T, is incredibly helpful and so sweet. Never strict on deadlines at all, if you can't get a paper in for the given date just let her know and she will gladly give you an extra week or so to get it in. Her lectures were pretty bland but overall she is an amazing teacher. SO understanding

Prof T. is my amazing! She's the sweetest lady I've ever met, takes the time to know everyone's names and really cares about your success. She's helped me with work from other classes, and work for hers. If you have the chance to take a class with her, you should! She gives participation marks, and she's willing to give extra time if you need it!
She was extremely understanding and a very clear professor. I would recommend her to any student in a heartbeat.
A prof who honestly cares about her students. For class, or whatever else.

Simply the best Professor I've had so far. She is so charming and such a sweet lady. I absolutely adore her and I wish she was my mother. She is extremely kind and asks how your day is, and she just makes the day better for you. Her marking is very detailed and you can tell she loves teaching with a passion.
Just an amazingly nice and smart lady. She made this course so easy for me with all of her help, sincerity and enthusiasm.  Also a super easy marker
Great prof., really cares about her students and is happy to help. Try to get into her DGD because she marks very easily! Her DGD students received much higher marks than the T.A.'s class did.

The best prof I have ever had. She is incredibly sweet and understanding and wants all of her students to succeed. Go to her office hours and talk to her about your projects, she will help you so much! Overall an amazing lady

Easily one of my favourite profs. Super sweet, learned everyone`s name, and provided helpful critique. If you go into this class knowing how to write an essay it is beyond easy - I attended 3 lectures over the course of the semester and received an A+.

Prof T as she likes to be referred to is one of the best profs you will ever have. Very understanding and thorough with each lecture and make sure you get her for the DGD! She is very lenient on due dates and never gives out late penalties if you communicate with her. Course pack was only a few dollars and the essays in it were pretty interesting!

She is only one of the nicest professors I've met. She really tries to get to know you, especially if you're not doing too well. She is a little bit critical when it comes to writing, but it's all constructive criticism, and personally develops you to be a better writer.
Incredible professor, highly recommended! Try to take her class, you won't regret it. She is so understanding and takes the time to know every single student's name.

She is truly incredible. She is incredibly kind, understanding and helpful. Although she is brilliant and it is very clear in her lectures, she never looks down on her students. Honestly a kind soul and an incredible professor. Taking her class will in no way be a regret!
Best prof ever. She let me have an extension for one of my essay papers. I honestly like her the most of all my profs
Personally asked me what I thought about her classes. That says it all. Would recommend to everyone.

Absolutely fascinating. Chooses very interesting material and is totally open for discussion. The courses she teaches are like a story tale in themselves. Has excellent historical background that lies the foundation for Our language. Personal and very genuine, considerate and too human to be human - Prof T. deserves the University's best attention.

Great teacher, really wants you to understand the material! She's always willing to give extensions, increase grades if you can argue that you deserve a higher mark and she's always happy to make time to answer any questions. Even if you don't like poetry, you should still take the course!
She is a great professor who is very nice and very open. She's very clear and really sweet. I'd recommend her to anyone and must say she's a gift to the University of Ottawa

She genuinely wants you to do good, and treats you as a person, not just another student number. She emails her own personal lecture notes to her students, along with her slides. She is a fair marker on essays, but her exams are a little tough, but nothing not covered in her notes. READ THE READINGS!Parcip. marks & makes class more entertaining :)

An absolute joy! She cares about her students,works hard to learn names and is very easy to relate to. Attend class! She bases almost everything on in class discussion. Made a mandatory class interesting!
most amazing teacher ever!! She really cares about how you do, really informative lectures and she's a very sweet lady!!!!
Great class! She's clearly very knowledgable on her subject and cares a lot about the students. I learned a lot in this course.
nicest professor in the university. Understanding of student workloads and pressures. goes out of her way to help you.

Poetry is really not my forte in all honesty just needed an english credit but she is easily one of the best professors i have had in university. clearly enjoys teaching and is unbelievably accommodating! wish more prof were like her. she makes you want to work hard. recommend taking her course even if you have no interest in the subject.

Super nice lady, always available and open for questions/extra help - kept in email contact with class for notes etc. which was really helpful!  Really cares about her subject and makes the class care about it too.  She marks on participation but classes aren't mandatory - still, they're well worth attending :)

She's absolutely fantastic!!! if you have the opportunity to take her class, I highly recommend it. She's the sweetest woman in the world and will do anything to help her students.  She made me see English and English Pofessors in a whole new light.

It was her first time teaching the subject, but you wouldn't know it based on how well her class was organized. Very helpful in and out of class. Classes were very naturally discussion based, without any forceful atmosphere of pressure. Lots of readings to do, but the workload is low, 2 test, 3 essays over a year (glad I had her for the whole year)
Loveliest woman on earth, I swear. Very sweet and not at all pretentious, and very understanding of student workloads. Teaches subject matter well. Loves quotes.
